#: ../../topics/configuration.rst:6
msgid "Configuring Salt"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topics/configuration.rst:8
msgid ""
"Salt configuration is very simple. The default configuration for the "
":term:`master` will work for most installations and the only requirement for"
" setting up a :term:`minion` is to set the location of the master in the "
"minion configuration file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topics/configuration.rst:14
msgid "master"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topics/configuration.rst:16
msgid ""
"The Salt master is the central server that all minions connect to. Commands "
"are run on the minions through the master, and minions send data back to the"
" master (unless otherwise redirected with a :doc:`returner "
"</ref/returners/index>`). It is started with the :command:`salt-master` "
"program."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topics/configuration.rst:21
msgid "minion"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topics/configuration.rst:23
msgid ""
"Salt minions are the potentially hundreds or thousands of servers that may "
"be queried and controlled from the master."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topics/configuration.rst:26
msgid ""
"The configuration files will be installed to :file:`/etc/salt` and are named"
" after the respective components, :file:`/etc/salt/master` and "
":file:`/etc/salt/minion`."
msgstr ""

